m Microsoft's ability to backdoor their own ASLR (or nearly anything else they produce for that matter). Also note their ASLR [\"feature\"](https://www.kb.cert.org/vuls/id/817544).\n\nRegarding your screenshot, how are you building the binary / which binary are you using?","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2018-03-02T05:12:22.721Z","updated_at":"2018-03-02T05:12:22.721Z","actor":{"username":"anonimal","cleared":false,"url":"/anonimal","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/040/857/f23cc3be09a21e17bc43975987c10ba2b6427239_original.png/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"monero","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":2448656,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"Note: I don't see any build hardening in the monero-gui https://github.com/monero-project/monero-gui/blob/master/monero-wallet-gui.pro.\n\n@c4c1234757b4f1e468a29d480d78f2 can you provide any monerod/monero-gui exploits that would otherwise be mitigated with ASLR?","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2018-03-02T05:21:58.815Z","updated_at":"2018-03-02T05:21:58.815Z","actor":{"username":"anonimal","cleared":false,"url":"/anonimal","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/040/857/f23cc3be09a21e17bc43975987c10ba2b6427239_original.png/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"monero","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":2449205,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"No I didn't build the master myself. I have only tested with the binary release on https://downloads.getmonero.org/gui/win64 . I was thinking this was the latest release. \n\nNo I'm not aware of any monerod/monero-gui exploits.","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2018-03-02T08:18:41.726Z","updated_at":"2018-03-02T08:18:41.726Z","actor":{"username":"flxflndy_","cleared":false,"url":"/flxflndy_","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/159/461/743e95b565d80b452431b1fa8d7ab60147fd6cd3_original.jpg/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":null},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"monero","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":2452782,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"As mentioned above, recent monerod uses ASLR, NX, PIE and -D_FORTIFY_SOURCE.\nThe GUI does not yet, this will be done soon. However, since the GUI only accesses the network when using a remote daemon or resolving openalias addresses, the attack surface is very much reduced.\n\nTo expand: the GUI will run the monerod binary to sync the blockchain and do general P2P comms. This is fully hardened. The GUI will access the network if it is set to use a remote daemon (not default). In this case, it will use the monero libraries, which are built with the hardening flags. This means most of the attack surface is hardened. However, the GUI specific C++ code is not yet hardened, and so this means it doesn't use things like ASLR. This code is mostly UI code though, so all the network code in shared libs is hardened.\n\nNote that I don't use windows, so I have no idea whether my hardening flags are really fully working for Windows. They're pretty good on Linux.\n","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2018-03-03T10:59:14.043Z","updated_at":"2018-03-03T10:59:14.043Z","actor":{"username":"moneromooo","cleared":false,"url":"/moneromooo","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"/assets/avatars/default-71a302d706457f3d3a31eb30fa3e73e6cf0b1d677b8fa218eaeaffd67ae97918.png"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":null},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"monero","actor_is_team_member":true,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":2453417,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"Ok, I've just build the master and checked that monerod is compiled with dynamicbase and run with ASLR on windows. (Although the current master fails to build and I had apply the changes from here https://github.com/monero-project/monero/issues/3296)\nI also agree that the GUI is not as important as the daemon.","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2018-03-03T19:21:34.117Z","updated_at":"2018-03-03T19:21:34.117Z","actor":{"username":"flxflndy_","cleared":false,"url":"/flxflndy_","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/159/461/743e95b565d80b452431b1fa8d7ab60147fd6cd3_original.jpg/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":null},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"monero","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":2455167,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"For the record, that conversation prodded me to finally rebuild a GUI VM and PR the hardening changes:\nhttps://github.com/monero-project/monero-gui/pull/1150\n","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2018-03-04T08:56:24.368Z","updated_at":"2018-03-04T08:56:24.368Z","actor":{"username":"moneromooo","cleared":false,"url":"/moneromooo","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"/assets/avatars/default-71a302d706457f3d3a31eb30fa3e73e6cf0b1d677b8fa218eaeaffd67ae97918.png"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":null},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"monero","actor_is_team_member":true,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":2461926,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::BugTriaged","message":"","automated_response":false,"cr